{{Quote|In hope of a better tomorrow, we cede control of the banks to the Office of the Chancellor of the Galactic Republic.|Senator [[Nix Card]], to the Galactic Senate|<ref name="Crisis at the Heart" />}}
The '''Office of the Chancellor''', also known as the '''office of the Supreme Chancellor''', consisted of the immediate staff of the [[Supreme Chancellor]] of the [[Galactic Republic]]. The second highest-ranking official in the office was the [[Vice Chair]]. In addition, a [[Chief of Staff]] and senior [[aide]]s assisted the chancellery with the administrative matters.

The Office of the Chancellor maintains both the [[Chancellery Secretariat]] beneath the Senate chambers of the [[Imperial Senate Building|Galactic Senate Building]] and the [[Emperor's office|Chancellor's office]] in the [[Imperial Executive Building|Senate Office Building]].

Following the [[death]] of [[Jedi Master]] [[Sifo-Dyas]] over the [[Oba Diah moon|moon]] of [[Oba Diah]], much of the information surrounding his demise was classified by the the administration of Chancellor [[Finis Valorum]]. The office's authority and influence expanded to an unprecedented level throughout the [[Clone Wars]], a process that began with the Galactic Senate empowering Valorum's successor, Chancellor [[Darth Sidious|Sheev Palpatine]], with wartime powers. In the aftermath of the [[Invasion of Scipio|Republic invasion]] of [[Scipio]], the chancellery gained control over the assets of the [[InterGalactic Banking Clan]]. The office was ultimately dissolved when Palpatine [[Proclamation of the New Order|proclaimed]] the formation of the [[Galactic Empire]], with himself as [[Galactic Emperor|Emperor]] of [[the galaxy]].

==Composition==
===Positions===
====Overview====
[[File:Palpatine19BBY.png|thumb|right|250px|The Supreme Chancellor (Chancellor Sheev Palpatine, pictured) sat as the head of the Office of the Chancellor.]]
The Office of the Chancellor was headed by the [[Supreme Chancellor]] of the [[Galactic Republic]] and based on the Republic [[capital]] [[planet]] of [[Coruscant]]<ref name="TLO" /> in the [[Core Worlds]].<ref name="Ultimate Star Wars">''[[Ultimate Star Wars]]''</ref> The [[Vice Chair]] was part of the office as vice chancellor in addition to their role as speaker of the [[Galactic Senate]].<ref name="Amedda">{{Databank|mas-amedda|Mas Amedda}}</ref> Furthermore, a position entitled "[[chair of the Senate]]" existed that could be held by the same individual who was the Vice Chair,<ref name="Vice Chair note">''[[Star Wars: The Complete Visual Dictionary, New Edition]]'' establishes that [[Mas Amedda]] first became [[Vice Chair]], or "Vice Chancellor" as ''[[Catalyst: A Rogue One Novel]]'' names it, during [[Supreme Chancellor]] [[Finis Valorum]]'s administration but continued to hold the title during [[Darth Sidious|Sheev Palpatine's]] administration. The events of [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''The Phantom Menace'']], which depicted the events of the [[Invasion of Naboo]] and the [[Supreme Chancellor election, 32 BBY|end of Valorum's reign]], are dated to [[32 BBY]] by ''[[Star Wars: Galactic Atlas]]''. The conversation in ''Catalyst'' where Amedda states he served as chair of the Senate a [[Standard decade|decade]] prior is dated to be eleven [[Standard year|years]] after the Invasion of Naboo, placing it in [[21 BBY]], which would mean Amedda served as chair of the Senate in [[31 BBY]]. Therefore, he must have been the Vice Chancellor and chair of the Senate at the same [[time]].</ref> although Supreme Chancellor [[Finis Valorum]] also referred to himself as "the chair" in his capacity as chancellor.<ref name="TPM">{{Film|I}}</ref> The senior administrative [[aide]] served the chancellor as an executive assistant.<ref name="Moore">{{SWCT|set=Base Series 1|cardname=Sly Moore - Chancellor's Aide}}</ref> In the waning [[Standard day|days]] of the Republic, a representative of the chancellery was appointed to the [[Jedi High Council]].<ref name="ROTS" />

====Greylark/Mollo chancellery====
{{Quote|Yes, well, I came as soon as the Office of the Frontier alerted me of your mission to Eiram. We sent you a tightbeam transmission, but when I did not hear back, I did what I thought best. I'm sure Chancellor Greylark will agree that we had to seize this opportunity. In our haste to intercept you, I was unable to update her of my change of plans. Not that I require her permission, of course.|Chancellor Orlen Mollo|<ref name="Convergence">''[[The High Republic: Convergence]]''</ref>}}
[[File:OrlenMolloKyongGreylark-TheChancellors.png|thumb|left|300px|Orlen Mollo and Kygong Greylark, Co-Chancellors of the Galactic Republic]]
During the days of [[Great Hyperspace Rush]] and Republic expansion period of the the [[High Republic Era]], the position of chancellor was held by two individuals&mdash;the [[human]] [[Kyong Greylark]] and the [[Quarren]] [[Orlen Mollo]]<ref name="Convergence" />&mdash;as Co-Chancellors.<ref name="Battle of Jedha">''[[The High Republic: The Battle of Jedha]]''</ref> Holding shared-power, the two chancellors set about governing the galactic differently. While Greylark remained on Coruscant, Mollo traveled across the [[Outer Rim Territories]] to help with the government's expansion and end crises. Both maintained separate offices, with the [[office of Chancellor Greylark]] taking credit for relief supplies brought to the [[Eiram and E'ronoh War|warring]] planets of [[E'ronoh]] and [[Eiram]] by her son, [[Axel Greylark]]. Axel was himself a figure of controversy and gossip over the [[HoloNet]]. In secret, Axel had ties with the [[Path of the Open Hand]] cult, whose leader, [[Elecia Zeveron|the Mother]], ordered him to steal vials of poison from the Eiram. Experiencing a change of heart after his time with [[Jedi Knight]] [[Gella Nattai]], [[Eirami]] [[prince]] [[Phan-tu Zenn]], and [[E'roni]] princess [[Xiri A'lbaran]], Axel decided to destroy the poison amid the [[Wedding of Phan-tu Zenn and Xiri A'lbaran]] by flooding the [[Erasmus Capital City]]. In the end, Axel was arrested and the destruction came to its end, with the peace between both worlds forged by the wedding still standing despite the incident and efforts of the rogue [[Children of E'ronoh]].<ref name="Convergence" />

Rather than have a direct Republic representative, Mollo elected to bring in [[Morton San Tekka]] as mediator of the [[Summit on Jedha|treaty signing summit]] over fears that having an elected official would be seen as Republic overreach. However, the summit was disrupted by the Path and devolved into the [[Battle of Jedha]].<ref name="Battle of Jedha" /> Efforts to again establish a ceasefire crossed over into the Republic and Jedi's investigation into the Path, whose members broke Axel out of prison on the order of the Mother. She hoped to leverage Axel's relationship with Chancellor Greylark into Path influence and thus had him send a message requesting she come to the Path homeworld of [[Dalna]]. Wanting to finally help her son while also not wanting to put the Republic at risk, Kyong did arrive, but only after giving up her title as Chancellor. Her action thus left Mollo the sole leader of the Republic, much to his shock, and ruined the Mother's plans. In the ensuing [[Night of Sorrow|Battle of Dalna]], the united forces of Eiram and E'ronoh aided the Jedi and Republic in battle, shattering the Path and re-establishing the ceasefire. Beyond beginning to forge a real connection with his mother, Axel also accepted his crimes and willingly returned to prison. While she promised to help out in the transition period, Kyong had no intentions of returning to office.<ref name="Cataclysm">''[[The High Republic: Cataclysm]]''</ref>

====Soh chancellery====
[[File:MatariSoh-2021THR1.png|thumb|right|250px|The chancellery under Soh was one of progess and hope.]]
Officials who served the office under Supreme Chancellor [[Lina Soh]]:
*[[Larep Reza]], Vice Chair of the [[The galaxy|Galactic]] Senate<ref name="The Rising Storm">''[[The High Republic: The Rising Storm]]''</ref>
*[[Jeffo Lorillia]], [[Secretary of Transportation]]<ref name="Light of the Jedi">''[[The High Republic: Light of the Jedi]]''</ref>
*[[Norel Quo]], primary aide of the Supreme Chancellor<ref name="Light of the Jedi" />

====Kalpana chancellery====
Officials who served the office under Supreme Chancellor [[Skor Kalpana]]:
*Finis Valorum, [[administrator]]<ref name="Tarkin">[[Tarkin (novel)|''Tarkin'']]</ref>

====Valorum chancellery====
[[File:ZodKneelsBeforeAmidala-TPMHD.jpg|thumb|left|250px|The Valorum chancellery was hindered by rampant corruption in the Galactic Senate.]]
Officials who served the office under Supreme Chancellor Finis Valorum:
*[[Mas Amedda]], Vice Chair of the Galactic Senate<ref name="Amedda" />
*[[Silman]], aide of the Supreme Chancellor<ref name="DB:S">{{Databank|silman|Silman}}</ref>
*[[Sei Taria]], aide of the Supreme Chancellor<ref name="Character Encyclopedia">''[[Star Wars Character Encyclopedia: Updated and Expanded]]''</ref>

====Palpatine chancellery====
[[File:Declaration.png|thumb|right|300px|Under the Palpatine chancellery, the Galactic Republic became the Galactic Empire.]]
Officials who served the office under Supreme Chancellor [[Darth Sidious|Sheev Palpatine]]:
*Mas Amedda, Vice Chair of the Galactic Senate<ref name="Amedda" />
*[[Ars Dangor]], [[Senior Advisor]] of the Supreme Chancellor<ref name="Rise" />
*[[Janus Greejatus]], Senior Advisor of the Supreme Chancellor<ref name="Rise" />
*[[Sly Moore]], [[Chief of Staff]]<ref name="RotS">''[[Rise of the Separatists]]''</ref> and senior administrative aide of the Supreme Chancellor<ref name="Moore" />
*[[Sate Pestage]], Senior Advisor of the Supreme Chancellor<ref name="Rise" />
*[[Anakin Skywalker]], [[Jedi Knight]], served as a representative to the [[Jedi]] High Council<ref name="ROTS" />

===Organizations===
[[File:Palpatine_on_balcony.jpg|thumb|left|250px|The Loyalist Committee served as an advisory board to the Office of the Chancellor.]]
During the [[Separatist Crisis]] and subsequent [[Clone Wars]], a number of organizations were associated with the Office of the Chancellor, including:
*[[Loyalist Committee]], a [[Politics|political]] board of [[loyalist]] [[senator]]s; formed to serve as an [[advisor]]y council to the Supreme Chancellor<ref name="Ultimate Star Wars" />
*[[InterGalactic Banking Clan]], a powerful commerce guild; ceded to the Office of the Chancellor following the [[Invasion of Scipio|Republic invasion]] of [[Scipio]]<ref name="InterGalactic Banking Clan">{{Databank|intergalactic-banking-clan|InterGalactic Banking Clan}}</ref><ref name="Crisis at the Heart" />

The Jedi High Council, though autonomous in the management of the internal affairs of the [[Jedi Order]],<ref name="DB Mace Windu">{{Databank|mace-windu|Mace Windu}}</ref> was bound by duty to serve the Senate.<ref name="ROTS" /> By extension, the Jedi served at the discretion of the Senate's elected leader, the Supreme Chancellor,<ref name="obiwanani1">[[Obi-Wan and Anakin 1|''Obi-Wan and Anakin'' 1]]</ref> but nonetheless maintained their direct allegiance to the galactic legislature.<ref name="ROTS" />

